# Git Interview Question

**1) What does git clone do **
```
Generally, it is used to get a copy of the remote repository to the local repository
```
***

**2) What does the command git config do? **
```
It allows you to view and modify various settings related to your Git repositories.

Setting user information.

git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your_email@example.com"

the appropriate flags (--global, --local)
```

**3) git rebase and git pull 
```
git pull:
The git pull command is used to fetch changes from a remote repository
and merge them into the current branch.

git rebase:
git rebase rewrites the commit history by moving or combining commits,
resulting in a linear history.

eg.
 git rebase master.
```

**4) git fetch
```
git fetch command that tells your local git to retrive the latest meta data
info from the the orignal (yet donesn't do any file transering)

just checking to see if there are any changes available.
```
